    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the Heller thing, but even the court said it's not an absolute right, right? like they acknowledged there can be limits. so if the legal side is basically a debate about where the line is, why does it feel like the argument for gun control is treated as more \"proven\" because of the crime stats, while the constitutional argument is just treated as something standing in the way of progress?",
